# Hibernate Persistent Life Cycle states 

 # There are four states
  1) Transient states
  2) Persistent states
  3) Detached state
  4) Removed state

  1) Transient state :
      - As soon as we create any object with respective fields to the objects by setting values with getter and setter the object immediatly
        goes into Transient state
      -Transient Object is hibernate is an object that is not associated with any hibernate session

